Comment: I loved and hated this movie. Good FX. Fantastic idea for plot. Acting was pretty good. Writing not so much. It's worth watching for the FX alone but they really missed the mark by making it a by the numbers planet disaster movie. I think someone mislabeled their "fresh ideas" outline and their "stay away from these cliches" outline. It's worth your time but keep those expectations in check and make full use of that "realism switch" in your head. Movies are not supposed to be 100% when it comes to survival but wow. Surviving space disasters was pushed to a whole new level. Have a watch and have fun. FYI. Everything that happens in space in the last 1/3 of the movie really pushes the limits even with my "yea that could happen" switch turned to 11. Then again most people ignore space junk now but come on!
